title: With measles, one vaccination protects many
description: Public health is communal. When you get a measles vaccine, you’re not just protecting yourself, but also others in society, including people who may not be able to receive the vaccine. Dr. Catharine Paules, an infectious diseases physician at Penn State Health, explains the concept of “herd immunity.”
